title: [Crack] JetBrains License Server v1.1
description:
JetBrains License Server v1.1 (Windows, Linux, Mac OS)

Description: Runs a local license server allowing you to register Ultimate/Professional versions of any JetBrains products.

Changes:
	- Added support for ReSharper Ultimate

GitHub Repo: https://github.com/CrackAttackz/JetBrainsLicenseServer/

Compatible Products (all versions):

IntelliJ IDEA - https://www.jetbrains.com/idea
PhpStorm - https://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm
PyCharm - https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm
RubyMine - https://www.jetbrains.com/ruby
WebStorm - https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm
AppCode - https://www.jetbrains.com/objc
CLion - https://www.jetbrains.com/clion
DataGrip - https://www.jetbrains.com/datagrip

ReSharper - https://www.jetbrains.com/resharper
ReSharper C++ - https://www.jetbrains.com/resharper-cpp
dotTrace - https://www.jetbrains.com/profiler
dotMemory - https://www.jetbrains.com/dotmemory
dotCover - https://www.jetbrains.com/dotcover
dotPeek - https://www.jetbrains.com/decompiler


Instructions:

NOTE: Licenses will expire after 48 hours if the license server has not been contacted! You will need to re-run the license server to obtain a new license. It is advised to keep the license server running while using the ReSharper suite.

- Extract zip file

Windows:
-------

1) In the "windows" folder run start_license_server.bat

This will open the JetBrains license server

2) In your JetBrains product menu, go to Help -> Register...

3) Select "License server"

4) Under "License server address:" enter in "http://localhost:9123"

5) Your product should now be licensed. You can close the license server window by selecting it and using Ctrl + C


Linux / Mac:
-----------

1) Change directory to the "linux-mac" folder

2) [Optional] Create a virtualenv and enter it

3) Run "pip install -r requirements.txt" to install required PyPI packages

4) Run "python ./jetbrains_license_server/manage.py runserver localhost:9123"

5) In your JetBrains product menu, go to Help -> Register...

6) Select "License server"

7) Under "License server address:" enter in "http://localhost:9123"

8) Your product should now be licensed. You can close the license server
